  "prompt": "How do I start thinking like the 2%?",
  "response": "Here are some key mindset shifts associated with top performers:\n\n1. Focus on solutions, not problems\n- Take ownership and responsibility\n- See challenges as opportunities for growth\n\n2. Continuous learning\n- Invest in personal development\n- Read extensively\n- Learn from failures and adapt quickly\n\n3. Long-term thinking\n- Set clear goals and strategic plans\n- Prioritize delayed gratification\n- Make decisions based on long-term impact\n\n4. High-value productivity\n- Prioritize tasks that create significant results\n- Eliminate low-value activities\n- Work smarter, not just harder\n\n5. Positive mindset\n- Cultivate resilience and optimism\n- Surround yourself with growth-oriented people\n- Practice gratitude\n\n6. Financial intelligence\n- Understand money management\n- Invest consistently\n- Create multiple income streams\n\n7. Health and energy management\n- Prioritize physical and mental wellness\n- Regular exercise\n- Quality sleep and nutrition\n\n8. Networking and relationships\n- Build genuine, mutually beneficial connections\n- Seek mentorship\n- Collaborate and add value to others\n\n9. Risk management\n- Calculate and take calculated risks\n- Embrace discomfort\n- Learn from mistakes\n\n10. Self-discipline and consistency\n- Develop strong habits\n- Stay committed to goals\n- Hold yourself accountable",
